INSERT INTO "stories" VALUES(9,'Standon Calling','We''ve been playing at the lovely Standon Calling festival for awhile now. Our first Dj adventure was a few years back, when we dragged a pair of big speakers into a tee-pee and threw a weekend long party. I remember hiring a van and lugging these fat speakers down there, only to discover as we set them up that there was already a wicked PA in the place for us to use...those speakers we''d carried about were used to balance a beer on for most of the weekend. I remember fairly early on the Friday evening getting away with playing a really fun old funk and soul style set, with a bit of rhythm and blues and classic rock and roll, ska, all sorts - really nice crowd to play to. The following year we came back, and the person hosting the tent - the poet Salena Godden was doing a poetry thing in the tee-pee during the day and into the evening before we DJ''d - had moved into a yurt. Colin, Matt and I dropped loads of tunes: I remember playing 50 Ways To Leave Your Lover and as the opening bars came in, a couple of blokes came over and were so into it, they did a spin-back on the first eight bars and we started the tune again - place loved it. Very funny. Then there was the year where the theme was Gods and Monsters: we took the bike out around the campsite, got loads of little parties going, and then went down into the area with the bars and food places and we had a laugh getting down in a field on a beautiful summers evening... So, Standon: see you there. ',2,'2016-03-04 23:46:35.090639','2016-03-04 23:46:35.090639',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
